## WhatsApp + ngrok Setup

### 1. Start ngrok

```bash
ngrok http 5000
```

Copy the `https://` URL — it changes every restart unless you have a paid static domain.

### 2. Meta Developer Dashboard

- Go to [developers.facebook.com](https://developers.facebook.com)
- Open your app → **WhatsApp** → **Configuration**
- Set **Callback URL** to: `https://your-ngrok-url.ngrok-free.app/webhook`
- Set **Verify Token** to match `VERIFY_TOKEN` in your `.env`
- Subscribe to webhook fields: `messages`, `message_deliveries`, `message_reads`

### 3. Get your WhatsApp token

- Go to **WhatsApp** → **API Setup**
- Copy the temporary access token (expires every 24 hours)
- For production: go to **Business Settings** → **System Users** → generate a permanent token with `whatsapp_business_messaging` permission

### 4. Verify

Hit this in your browser to confirm everything is connected:
```
https://your-ngrok-url.ngrok-free.app/health
```

