## API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET | `/health` | Server status |
| GET | `/webhook` | WhatsApp webhook verify |
| POST | `/webhook` | Incoming WhatsApp messages |
| GET | `/users` | All users |
| GET | `/messages/<phone>` | Messages for a user |
| POST | `/send` | Send a text message |
| POST | `/send-file` | Send a file |
| POST | `/toggle/<phone>` | Toggle AI/Human mode |
| POST | `/update-user` | Update user tags and notes |
| GET | `/analytics` | Analytics data |
| GET | `/export/csv` | Export all conversations |
| GET | `/export/csv?phone=X` | Export one conversation |
| POST | `/reload-knowledge` | Reload knowledge.txt |

---

## Human vs AI Mode

- **AI mode** (default) — bot reads the message and replies automatically using OpenRouter
- **Human mode** — bot is silent, you reply manually from the dashboard

Toggle per user using the **Switch to Human / Switch to AI** button in the chat header.

---

## Notes

- The SQLite database is created automatically on first run
- Media files sent from the dashboard are uploaded to WhatsApp and then deleted locally
- The `_processed_ids` set prevents duplicate webhook calls from Meta being handled twice
- The dashboard secret (`X-Dashboard-Token` header) protects all API routes
- Never commit your `.env` files — only commit `.env.example`